Based on my thorough audit of the FlowGuard frontend codebase, I've identified numerous responsive design issues across CSS files and components. Here's the comprehensive report:

---

## FLOWGUARD FRONTEND RESPONSIVE DESIGN AUDIT REPORT

### CRITICAL ISSUES FOUND: 22 Major Issues | 35 Minor Issues

---

## **FILE-BY-FILE ANALYSIS**

### **1. NAVBAR.CSS** (C:\Users\felth\Downloads\FlowGuard\client\src\css\NavBar.css)

**Issue 1.1: Excessive horizontal padding breaks on mobile**
- **Location:** Line 6 - `.navbar-container`
- **Problem:** `padding: 15px 60px` sets 60px horizontal padding. At 375px viewport, this leaves only 255px for content.
- **Breakpoints affected:** Mobile (375px), Tablet (768px)
- **Fix needed:** 
```css
@media (max-width: 375px) {
  .navbar-container {
    padding: 12px 10px; /* Reduce to 10px on ultra-small screens */
  }
}
```

**Issue 1.2: Logo font size not responsive**
- **Location:** Line 22 - `.nav-logo`
- **Problem:** Fixed `font-size: 1.5rem` (24px) may be too large on mobile (375px)
- **Breakpoints affected:** Mobile (375px)
- **Fix needed:**
```css
@media (max-width: 375px) {
  .nav-logo {
    font-size: 1.2rem; /* Scale down from 1.5rem */
  }
}
```

**Issue 1.3: Missing medium breakpoint (768px to 1024px)**
- **Location:** Lines 114-134
- **Problem:** Media query only targets max-width 768px. Gap between 768px-1024px tablets has no rules.
- **Breakpoints affected:** Tablet (800px, 920px)
- **Fix needed:**
```css
@media (max-width: 1024px) and (min-width: 769px) {
  .navbar-container {
    padding: 15px 30px;
  }
  .nav-status-pill {
    padding: 6px 12px;
  }
}
```

**Issue 1.4: Nav login button padding inconsistent**
- **Location:** Lines 99-112 and 136-157 (duplicate CSS rules)
- **Problem:** Button defined twice with different padding values. At mobile, button is 10px 24px but may be too large in tap target.
- **Breakpoints affected:** Mobile (375px)
- **Fix needed:** Consolidate and add:
```css
@media (max-width: 480px) {
  .nav-login-btn {
    padding: 10px 14px;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }
}
```

---

### **2. DASHBOARD.CSS** (C:\Users\felth\Downloads\FlowGuard\client\src\css\Dashboard.css)

**Issue 2.1: Sidebar fixed width breaks layout at medium screens**
- **Location:** Lines 34-35 - `.sidebar`
- **Problem:** `width: 240px; min-width: 240px;` is not flexible. At 768px tablet, leaves only 528px for content.
- **Breakpoints affected:** Tablet (768px)
- **Fix needed:**
```css
@media (max-width: 1024px) {
  .sidebar {
    width: 200px;
    min-width: 200px;
  }
}
```

**Issue 2.2: Grid columns too rigid at tablet**
- **Location:** Lines 206-210 - `.top-summary-row`
- **Problem:** 3-column grid at desktop, 2-column at 1024px (line 469), but no intermediate for 768px-1024px range. Cards may be cramped.
- **Breakpoints affected:** Tablet (768px-900px)
- **Fix needed:**
```css
@media (max-width: 900px) and (min-width: 769px) {
  .top-summary-row {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  }
  .activity-cards-grid {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
  }
}
```

**Issue 2.3: Activity cards grid missing responsive breakpoint**
- **Location:** Lines 241-246 - `.activity-cards-grid`
- **Problem:** 4-column at desktop, jumps to 2-column at 1024px, but no explicit mobile (1fr) rule until line 553-555.
- **Breakpoints affected:** Tablet (768px-1023px)
- **Fix needed:** Add explicit rule at 768px.

**Issue 2.4: Bar chart label overflow at mobile**
- **Location:** Lines 281-313 - `.mock-bar-chart` and `.bar-wrapper span`
- **Problem:** Chart height is 200px fixed with absolute positioned labels at `bottom: -25px`. At 375px, labels may overflow or clip.
- **Breakpoints affected:** Mobile (375px)
- **Fix needed:**
```css
@media (max-width: 480px) {
  .mock-bar-chart {
    height: 150px;
  }
  .bar-wrapper span {
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    bottom: -20px;
  }
}
```

**Issue 2.5: Camera grid minmax too large**
- **Location:** Lines 331-335 - `.camera-grid`
- **Problem:** `minmax(320px, 1fr)` means cards never shrink below 320px. At 375px mobile with padding, only 1 card fits.
- **Breakpoints affected:** Mobile (375px)
- **Fix needed:**
```css
@media (max-width: 480px) {
  .camera-grid {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  }
}
```

**Issue 2.6: Mobile menu button positioning conflicts**
- **Location:** Lines 476-493
- **Problem:** Mobile menu button is `position: fixed; top: 15px; left: 15px;` but sidebar hamburger needs close button coordination. At small widths, may overlap content.
- **Breakpoints affected:** Mobile (375px)
- **Fix needed:** Ensure z-index stacking and adjust sidebar width:
```css
@media (max-width: 375px) {
  .mobile-menu-btn {
    width: 40px;
    height: 40px;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
  }
  .dashboard-main {
    padding: 70px 15px 20px; /* Adjust for smaller hamburger */
  }
}
```

**Issue 2.7: Incident row gap too wide at mobile**
- **Location:** Lines 411-421 - `.incident-row`
- **Problem:** `gap: 30px` is excessive on 375px screens (only 15px left for actual content if icon takes 30px).
- **Breakpoints affected:** Mobile (375px)
- **Fix needed:**
```css
@media (max-width: 480px) {
  .incident-row {
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 15px;
  }
}
```

---

### **3. HOME.CSS** (C:\Users\felth\Downloads\FlowGuard\client\src\css\Home.css)

**Issue 3.1: Hero title font size unresponsive**
- **Location:** Lines 55-63 - `.hero-title`
- **Problem:** Fixed `font-size: 4rem` (64px). On 375px screen, this is 17% of viewport width and causes severe horizontal overflow.
- **Breakpoints affected:** Mobile (375px), Tablet (768px)
- **Fix needed:**
```css
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .hero-title {
    font-size: 2.2rem;
  }
}
@media (max-width: 480px) {
  .hero-title {
    font-size: 1.8rem;
  }
}
```

**Issue 3.2: Hero description not responsive**
- **Location:** Lines 65-71 - `.hero-description`
- **Problem:** Fixed `font-size: 1.2rem` with `max-width: 800px` padding. At 375px, 20px padding leaves only 335px for 1.2rem text.
- **Breakpoints affected:** Mobile (375px)
- **Fix needed:**
```css
@media (max-width: 480px) {
  .hero-description {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }
}
```

**Issue 3.3: Stats grid doesn't respond to tablet (768px)**
- **Location:** Lines 115-122 - `.stats-grid`
- **Problem:** `minmax(300px, 1fr)` means at 768px with padding, only 2 cards fit. No explicit rule at 768px breakpoint.
- **Breakpoints affected:** Tablet (768px)
- **Fix needed:**
```css
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .stats-grid {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  }
}
```

**Issue 3.4: Stat value font size too large at mobile**
- **Location:** Lines 143-148 - `.stat-value`
- **Problem:** Fixed `font-size: 3rem` on 375px screens is 8% of viewport—too dominant and causes wrapping.
- **Breakpoints affected:** Mobile (375px)
- **Fix needed:**
```css
@media (max-width: 480px) {
  .stat-value {
    font-size: 2rem;
  }
}
```

**Issue 3.5: Feature cards grid unresponsive at tablet**
- **Location:** Lines 296-300 - `.features-grid`
- **Problem:** `minmax(300px, 1fr)` with only 768px-width media query. At 850px, may have awkward 2-col layout.
- **Breakpoints affected:** Tablet (768px-900px)
- **Fix needed:**
```css
@media (max-width: 900px) and (min-width: 769px) {
  .features-grid {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
  }
}
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .features-grid {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  }
}
```

