message.content:
This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.

Summary:
1. Primary Request and Intent:
   The user is Felicia Tan (NYP IT2115-03 Group 11), working on FlowGuard's Module 1: Facial Recognition & Access Management. Across this session, they requested:
   - Add manual photo upload (3 angles) to FaceEnrollment.jsx alongside the existing webcam flow
   - Fix attendance clock-out not updating "Total Personnel On-Site" metric
   - Make camera feeds (V-Patrol + GateScanner) square with aspect-ratio: 1/1
   - Fix horizontal scroll on Gate Terminal mobile
   - Apply critical mobile (375px/480px) responsive fixes to Home.css, Enrollment.css, AIChatPopup.css
   - Make V-Patrol layout viewport-contained (no page scroll, timeline scrolls internally)
   - Apply same constrained layout to GateScanner
   - Make the card container itself square (not just the camera inside it)
   - Reduce V-Patrol gap between camera and timeline cards to 12px
   - Fix gap override in media query (was `gap: 20px` at ≤1024px overriding the `gap: 12px` base rule)
   - **Currently active:** Fix cards overflowing their container bounds — camera card and timeline card extend beyond the "red box" boundary area

2. Key Technical Concepts:
   - React + Vite frontend, Node.js/Express backend, Python FastAPI AI service (InsightFace)
